<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 07 at 4:00PM EDT  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Wabash,
southwestern Noble, Whitley, northern Huntington and southeastern
Kosciusko Counties through 430 PM EDT...
At 359 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
North Manchester, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph. Heavy downpours, road ponding
and localized nuisance flooding possible.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Pierceton around 410 PM EDT.
South Whitley around 415 PM EDT.
Other locations in the path of this storm include Columbia City.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
